social_posts.post_text: My New Year always starts in November. This years theme is to BE exactly who I am and love it with no interruption. This is the body post but I stay working on the mind and soul daily (#IYKYK). We can create the life we want friends you can have that career you want, that car, that home, that health.. We can look younger and feel it too so go off and make life count! I give you permission and celebrate you .. be fearless 🎉💞 #MakeItCount #Fearless

One thing I’ll always give myself is credit for staying disciplined with my body. My body is my temple and it’s been a blessing to have it as my vessel for this lifetime. I’ve stayed ready for the summer my whole life. I will continue to treat her good and keep her sacred. I’m so grateful for this life I live, mindset I have and vessel that is mine 💞💫👙 #BikiniLifeForever

Have you ever felt a strong energetic charge towards someone or something? It can be a powerful force, but sometimes we have to step back and examine what it’s really about....

In the creative industry, harnessing this energy of attraction can fuel our creative endeavors. Whether it’s collaborating with someone whose work we admire, or being drawn to qualities we desire to embody ourselves, this attraction can lead to amazing outcomes as long as we don’t get confused or distracted by them.

That’s why in our FAN: FREQUENCY ACTIVATE NOW PROGRAM we share the tools you need to harness these strong feelings of attraction into the creative output they are meant to be, without all the confusion. These trainings are a form of emotional alchemy, helping you to transform and transmute any energetic blocks so you can create with even greater flow and ease. 

Are you ready to unlock your creative potential? 💫

I’m excited to announce I’ll be speaking on the panel this Friday the 29th for the #FutureOfMusic Summit. Tickets still available. We’d love to see you there 🫶🏼

I got to speak on a panel with some incredible peers @johnsonout (producer, drummer, legend and friend), @mlewey (your favorite songwriters favorite songwriter) and @natashaustere (seasoned music marketing strategist and epic soul). I met some spiritually enlightened kids with the abilities to make all their dreams and goals happen. I just came to shed some some wisdom in hopes that they’ll evolve past what I’ve ever done faster and with the support of someone who has been where they’re going. @futureofmusicsummit thank you for having me! I’m extremely grateful to pay it forward. That’s what life is about 💕

Omg if you know me well I don’t love to be asked to sing on the spot. I’ve been asked my whole life to do it😬 it’s a singers cue to crawl into a shell HOWEVER anything for @kaitlindiaries haha! This interview was so deep and powerful. We touched on some really spiritual layers of existence! Kait, I love you mama. Thank you for having me and s/o @kandyhousela for always showing love. As much as I messed up the lyrics and made my first ever appearance as “shy” this was soooo fun 🤩 LINK IN BIO P.S. isn’t Kait STUNNING 😍
